interactions.prompt:
You are given a number of summaries which need to be grouped by their semantic commonalities. 
Each summary needs to be grouped and each group contains at most 5 summaries. 
The output has the following format: 
{"first group name": list of summaries in that group e.g. ["some question", "a second question"], "second group name": list of its members e.g. ["some third question"]}. 
Only output the groups with their members without any explanation or additional information. 

SUMMARIES:
{"Violation Method": "The violation method was not specified.", "Affected Subject(s)": "The affected subject(s) include Land, Water, Air, Worker, and Documents.", "Violation Description": "Please provide a detailed description of the violation, including any specific directions if necessary.", "Reporter Contact Information": "You are not required to provide your contact information but the EPA might want to reach out to you for additional information. Please fill out the following fields: Your Name, Your Email, Your Phone Number."}

 The output needs to fit the following Regular Expression:
 \{[\s
]*("[^\}]+":[\s
]*\[[^\}]+\][\s
]*,{0,1}[\s
]*)*[\s
]*\}

